3 CONC vi ously known as First Congregational Church. The present building da
3 CONC te s from 1814 and was built over part of the burying ground. Some gra
3 CONC ves tones remain in the basement crypt, and may be visited from 11 a
3 CONC m t o 1 pm Thursdays and Saturdays for tours. Many people were burie
3 CONC d on t he green; in 1821 almost all of the remaining outside monument
3 CONC s were m oved to Grove Street Cemetery (at Grove Street many of thos
3 CONC e tombstone s are around the inside wall in alphabetical order.)
