3 CONC o r of New York City. Arriving in 1632 on "The Lion" (with a religiou
3 CONC s s eparatist movement that called themselves "The Saints", that fle
3 CONC d Engl and to Leydon, Holland then went back to England to follow th
3 CONC e Mayflow er voyage), Thomas Willett was a merchant that traded from P
3 CONC lymouth Co lony, Massachusetts. He succeeded Captain Miles Standish a
3 CONC s head of th e Colonial Militia and negotiated what is now known as th
